We design Flint to be portable.


== RHEL/CentOS 6

The default g++ package is too old to build Flint.
A workaround for the issue is using devtoolset-6's g++.
Find instructions to install and use it in
<https://www.softwarecollections.org/en/scls/rhscl/devtoolset-6/>.

Moreover, some packages are necessary:
$ sudo yum install wget \
    java-1.7.0-openjdk-devel gtk2-devel libuuid-devel libxml2-devel


== RHEL/CentOS 7

Install necessary tools for building and installing Flint with:
$ sudo yum install gcc gcc-c++ autoconf automake libtool cmake wget \
    java-1.7.0-openjdk-devel gtk3-devel libuuid-devel libxml2-devel


== Debian Stretch/Buster/Sid

We do not have a Debian package (.deb) for Flint yet.
Before building Flint, you will want to install prerequisite Debian packages
as follows:
$ sudo apt-get install gcc g++ autoconf automake libtool cmake openjdk-8-jdk \
    pkgconf libgtk2.0-dev libxml2-dev


== Fedora 24

Use dnf(8) to install required packages for building Flint:
$ sudo dnf install gcc gcc-c++ autoconf automake libtool cmake wget \
    java-1.8.0-openjdk libuuid-devel libxml2-devel gtk3-devel


== Ubuntu 16.04 LTS (Xenial Xerus)

$ sudo apt install g++ autoconf automake libtool cmake openjdk-8-jdk \
    libgtk2.0-dev libxml2-dev uuid-dev


== Ubuntu 14.04.3 LTS (Trusty Tahr)

All you have to do for installing necessary tools is:
$ sudo apt-get install g++ autoconf automake libtool cmake openjdk-7-jdk \
    libgtk2.0-dev libxml2-dev uuid-dev


